50|$|Some N-halogenated {{derivatives}} of hydantoin {{are used}} as chlorinating or brominating agents in disinfectant/sanitizer or biocide products. The three major N-halogenated derivatives are <b>dichlorodimethylhydantoin</b> (DCDMH), bromochlorodimethylhydantoin (BCDMH), and dibromodimethylhydantoin (DBDMH). A mixed ethyl-methyl analogue, 1,3-dichloro-5-ethyl-5-methylimidazolidine-2,4-dione (bromochloroethylmethylhydantoin), is also used in mixtures with the above.|$|E

